  "doc_id": "48661",
  "text": "One possible way of obtaining a priori tropospheric gradients is to calculate them using the output of a NWM. In this work, we have tested using gradients calculated from ERA-Interim [CITATION_1] ), see Sect. 2.2 for details. If we fix the gradients to these values in the data analysis of the Intensives, the WRMS of the UT1-UTC difference relative to the reference solution marginally decreases from 21.8 to 21.4 µs for the INT1 sessions. When looking at the LOD difference between the Intensives and IGS, we also find decreases in the WRMS differences: for the INT1 sessions from 26.2 to 25.5 µs, and from 25.4 to 24.4 µs for the INT2 sessions.",
